				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">1: You should really leave that up to the end-user, eg. my PAL tv clips the first scanline, shows all bottom scanlines, and clips some pixels on the left and right. No matter how many pixels are clipped by the tv, the NES renders all of them, so you shouldn't discard your Sprite0Hit and LostSprites.
<br />
<br />2: No, if it's not rendered, the flag is not set. Though that's only possible if the current sprite address isn't 0. *edit* come to think of it, the 8 sprites limit can actually never even affect sprite 0.
<br />
<br />3: just the current line</div>

